(1082, '_transient_dash_aa95765b5cc111c56d5993d476b1c2f0', '<div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://ma.tt/2015/02/elon-musk-ama/'' title=''I am Elon Musk, CEO/CTO of a rocket company, AMA!. This guy continues to amaze. [&hellip;]''>Matt: Elon Musk AMA</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://ma.tt/2015/02/actually-good-youtube-comment/'' title=''Hey guys! I found a good comment on Youtube. Documenting here for posterity, from vTxTobi: Top 5 rappers: 1. Kendrick Lamar 2. K.dot 3. Guy in second verse of Control 4. Short dude in TDE 5. The good kid in a mad city (I added the links.) The joke is all of those refer to Kendrick Lamar, so was laugh-out-loud funny. It was on Kendrick’s powerful and controve [&hellip;]''>Matt: Actually Good Youtube Comment</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://ma.tt/2015/02/future-of-wp-and-jetpack/'' title=''There’s been some interesting threads going around on Jetpack and the future of WordPress, here’s Chris Lema’s take: Is the Future Success of WordPress tied to Jetpack?. [&hellip;]''>Matt: Future of WP and Jetpack</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wptavern.com/wpglobus-plugin-adds-a-language-switcher-to-wordpress'' title=''Last week WPGlobus 1.0 beta was released on WordPress.org. The plugin offers an interesting new attempt at providing multi-language support for WordPress sites. WPGlobus allows you to configure a set of available languages and adds a dropdown language switcher to the frontend via a custom menu. The development team behind WPGlobus is led by WordPress develop [&hellip;]''>WPTavern: WPGlobus Plugin Adds a Language Switcher to WordPress</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wptavern.com/new-plugin-detects-shared-terms-in-wordpress-ahead-of-taxonomy-term-splitting-in-4-2'' title=''photo credit: Utičnice – (license) Taxonomy term splitting in WordPress 4.2 addresses a seven-year-old bug that occasionally posed a nuisance to developers. In the past, WordPress allowed terms to be shared between multiple taxonomies. This caused a problem where updating a shared term would change the others unintentionally. Boone Gorges’ progress on this t [&hellip;]''>WPTavern: New Plugin Detects Shared Terms in WordPress Ahead of Taxonomy Term Splitting in 4.2</a></li></ul></div>', 'no'),
